    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>Comments</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>We collect the data given in the comments form, as well as the visitor&apos;s IP address and browser user agent string, to aid spam detection.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>The Gravatar service may be given an anonymized string created from your email address (also known as a hash) to see if you are using it. The Gravatar privacy statement can be found at https://automattic.com/privacy/. Your profile image is shown to the public in the context of your comment after it has been approved.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong>Cookies</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>You can choose to save your name, email address, and website in cookies if you leave a comment on our site. These are for your convenience so you don&apos;t have to enter your information again when you write another remark. This batch of cookies will last a year.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>If you log in to this site with an account, we will set a temporary cookie to see if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie includes no personal information and is deleted when your browser is closed.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>We will set up numerous cookies when you log in to save your login information and screen display preferences. Cookies for login and screen options last for two days and a year, respectively. Your login will be saved for two weeks if you choose &quot;Remember Me.&quot; The login cookies will be deleted if you log out of your account.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>If you update or publish an article, your browser will save an extra cookie. This cookie contains no personal information and just indicates the article&apos;s post ID. It is only valid for one day.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong>Other websites&apos; information embedded</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>This site&apos;s articles may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded material from other websites behaves exactly as if the visitor had visited that site.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>These websites may collect information about you, utilise cookies, embed extra third-party tracking, and track your interactions with embedded content, including tracking your interactions with embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong>How long do we keep your information?</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>If you make a comment, it will be saved eternally, along with its information. This is so that any subsequent comments will be recognised and approved automatically rather than being held in a moderation queue.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>Users that register on our website (if any) contribute personal information in their user profile, which we retain. At any moment, any user can see, modify, or remove their personal information (except they cannot change their username). The information can also be viewed and edited by website administrators.</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong>What control do you have over your personal information?</strong></p>
    <p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0cm;line-height:115%;font-size:16px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'>You can request an exported file of the personal data we possess about you, including any data you have provided to us, if you have an account on our site or have posted comments. You can also ask us to delete any personal information we have about you. This excludes any information that we are required to store for administrative, legal, or security reasons.</p>
